 "text": "Chart)\n\nUSSR: Soviet naval forces have concluded the large-scale combined air/surface/submarine exercise in the Norwegian Sea which began 11-12 August. Four cruiser-destroyer groups and a large number of submarines--probably over forty--participated in one of the largest Soviet out-of-area exercises yet noted. Numerous BADGER jet medium bomber aircraft also took part, with a high of 73 sorties scheduled during one 24-hour period. Most of the participating units were from the Northern Fleet, but one group of surface ships and two submarines from the Baltic Fleet were involved. Exercises of this type, defense of the seaward approaches to the Murman coast, are usually conducted twice a year", "token_count": 109, "token_end_0based": 234, "token_start_0based": 126, "token_text": "chart ussr soviet naval forces have concluded the large-scale combined air surface submarine exercise in the norwegian sea which began 11-12 august four cruiser-destroyer groups and a large number of submarines probably over forty participated in one of the largest soviet out-of-area exercises yet noted numerous badger jet medium bomber aircraft also took part with a high of 73 sorties scheduled during one 24-hour period most of the participating units were from the northern fleet but one group of surface ships and two submarines from the baltic fleet were involved exercises of this type defense of the seaward approaches to the murman coast are usually conducted twice a year", "unred_source_page": 4}
